messages.original: A large fire is burning in Kozyatyn, Vinnytsia Oblast after it was hit by ~3 Kh-101 cruise missiles. Power outages are reported.

A 5-story apartment building has partially collapsed in Darnystia District of Kyiv. At least 3 civilians were killed. 
The level of damage the building recieved, which is made of brick (unlike the much stronger reinforced concrete apartments), suggests that it may have been hit by a downed missile. Additionally, no missile strikes were reported in east bank Kyiv.
A large fire is burning in Kozyatyn, Vinnytsia Oblast after it was hit by ~3 Kh-101 cruise missiles. Power outages are reported.

NASA FIRMS data shows that large fires are burning at the Kozyatyn Locomotive Depot after it was hit by Kh-101 cruise missiles and Geran-2 drones. A photo from the scene showing a burnt-out train corroborates this.

Russian forces have captured the town of Udachne, western flank of Pokrovsk, Donetsk Oblast. 
Pre-war population: ~1,633.
Total land area: ~3.41 km¬≤.
The battles for Udachne lasted approximately 225 days.
Flight of a Geran-3 jet drone over Kyiv this morning. This is likely the first ever footage of a Geran-3 in action

Footage showing two Ukrainian GUR FPV drone strikes on a Russian Buyan-M class corvette of the Black Sea Fleet in the Sea of Azov, off the coast of Crimea. The drones targeted the vessel's communication and radar systems. 
The video is reportedly from today, which is corroborated by the fact that a Buyan-M corvette has been active in this exact area for the past few days.

The missile was an S-300, targeting Ukrainian UAVs.

At least five Israeli airstrikes targeted the Al-Khardali Valley in southern Lebanon a short time ago. The IDF spokesperson stated that they were targeting Hezbollah military infrastructure, including a rocket launcher position.

One of the targets from Russia's combined missile and drone attack on Kyiv was a factory producing Bayraktar long-range UAVs. It was hit by 1-2 missiles, likely Iskander-M ballistics, although it has reportedly previously been hit as many as 3 times in the past six months.

Ukrzaliznytsia published clearer photos of the destroyed passenger train at the at the Kozyatyn Locomotive Depot in Vinnytsia Oblast. As usual, the camera is facing away from the impact point. The depot was targeted by both Kh-101 cruise missiles and Geran-2 drones.

In the early hours of this morning, a Russian BEK (sea drone) struck the Ukrainian Navy's medium reconnaissance ship ‚ÄúSimferopol‚Äù at the mouth of the Danube River near the southern tip of Odesa Oblast. 
The Russian MOD claimed that the ship sunk, while the Ukrainian Navy Spokesperson Dmytro Pletenchuk confirmed the strike and stated that efforts to extinguish fires are ongoing. He reported that the "vast majority" of the crew are safe, but that one was killed, and several others are injured and missing. Search and rescue operations are ongoing. 
The vessel is one of the largest in the Ukrainian Navy, even before 2022.
